{"lemma":"عِبْرَةُ","slug":"عِبْرَةُ","root":"ع.ب.ر","root_slug":"ع-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عِبْرَة","root":"عبر","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n27822","n27832","n27833"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"example, lesson, warning","examples":[{"text":"لَقَدْ كَانَ فِي قَصَصِهِمْ عِبْرَةٌ لِأُولِي الْأَلْبَابِ","english":"There is a lesson in the stories of such people for those who understand."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a tear before it overflows, a sobbing, the first sign of weeping","examples":[{"text":"فَفَاضَت دُمُوعُ الْجَحْمَتَيْنِ بِعَبْرَةٍ … عَلَى الزُبِّ حَتَّى الزُبِّ فِي المَاءِ غَامِس","english":"And the tears of the two eyes overflowed without sobbing … over the beard, until the beard was dipping into water"},{"text":"أسندتْ رأسها إلى صدري وسالت عبراتها.","english":"She leant her head on my chest where slight tears flew."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ع ب ر (ʕ b r). Compare to عَبْر (ʕabr, “crossing”)."},"ipa":["/ʕib.ra/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27822","headword_ar":"عَبَرَهُ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborN","text_ar":"عَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubuwrN","text_ar":"عُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [the latter of which is the more common,] (S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He crossed it, went across it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed over it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from one side thereof to the other;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K;) namely, a river, (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K, *) and a valley, (K, TA,) &c. (S, Mgh.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara bihi","text_ar":"عَبَرَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaA='a","text_ar":"المَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara Als~abiyla","text_ar":"عَبَرَ السَّبِيلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubuwrN","text_ar":"عُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He travelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed along, the way,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K; *) as though he cut it, or furrowed it. (K, * TK.) ―         -b4-  And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara","text_ar":"عَبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor. as above, S,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, Msb, K:) as though he travelled the road of life: or, as F says in the B, as though he crossed over the bridge of the present world or life. (TA.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"faA_ino naEoburo faA_in~a lanaA lumaAtK\n                      \n                     \n                        waA_ino nagoburo fanaHonu EalaY nu*uwri"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"So if we die, there are others like to us; and if we remain alive, we are"},{"kind":"text","text":"waiting for that which must necessarily come to pass, as though we were"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bound by vows"},{"kind":"text","text":"to meet it. (S, O.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabarati Als~aHaAy^ibu","text_ar":"عَبَرَتِ السَّحَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EubuwrN","text_ar":"عُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The clouds travelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed along, quickly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara Alr~uw^oyaA","text_ar":"عَبَرَ الرُّوْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 2, in two places. ―         -b2-  And [hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabarotu AlT~ayora","text_ar":"عَبَرْتُ الطَّيْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborN","text_ar":"عَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zajarotuhaA","text_ar":"زَجَرْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I augured from the flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"alighting-places,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cries,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the birds;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I made the birds to fly away in order that I might augur from their flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (O, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara AlkitaAta","text_ar":"عَبَرَ الكِتَاتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborN","text_ar":"عَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (As, S, A, * O, K, *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He meditated upon, endeavouring to understand it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he considered, examined,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"studied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, O, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he read mentally,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing, not raising his voice in doing so,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, A, O, K,) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in reading it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baEoDa","text_ar":"بَعْضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotabara","text_ar":"اِعْتَبَرَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlkitaAbi bibaEoDK","text_ar":"الكِتَابِ بِبَعْضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabarahu","text_ar":"عَبَرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He considered and compared one part of the book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"writing, with another part, in order to understand it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara AlmataAEa","text_ar":"عَبَرَ المَتَاعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~araAhima","text_ar":"الدَّرَاهِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborN","text_ar":"عَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He examined what was the weight of the goods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the dirhems, and what they were."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~araAhima fawajadotuhaA A^alofFA","text_ar":"الدَّرَاهِمَ فَوَجَدْتُهَا اَلْفًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotabarotu","text_ar":"اِعْتَبَرْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabarotuhaA","text_ar":"عَبَرْتُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I tried,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"examined, the dirhems, and found them to be a thousand."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b5-  See also 8, second sentence.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabira","text_ar":"عَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabarN","text_ar":"عَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara","text_ar":"عَبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborN","text_ar":"عَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) [but the former seems to be the more correct, as will be seen from what follows;] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstEbr","text_ar":"استعبر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, O, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He shed tears; his eyes,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"eye, watered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabirato Eayonuhu","text_ar":"عَبِرَتْ عَيْنُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His eye shed tears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"watered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AstEbrt","text_ar":"استعبرت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabira","text_ar":"عَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabarN","text_ar":"عَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (AZ, T, O, * L, TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabara","text_ar":"عَبَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaborN","text_ar":"عَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K; [but see above;])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He grieved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mourned; was sorrowful, sad,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unhappy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, T, O, L, K, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA lahu sahira waEabira","text_ar":"مَا لَهُ سَهِرَ وَعَبِرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What aileth him? May he be sleepless by night, and may he grieve,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mourn:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1937},{"kind":"text","text":"is a form of imprecation against a man, used by the Arabs. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eabirato","text_ar":"عَبِرَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabarN","text_ar":"عَبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She became bereft of her child,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"children, by death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuborN","text_ar":"عُبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","O","Msb","K","TA","As","A"]},{"entry_id":"n27832","headword_ar":"عَبْرَةٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaArapN","text_ar":"عِبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A tear:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tear before it overflows:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sobbing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reiteration"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sound"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of weeping in the bosom:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an overflowing of tears without the sound of weeping:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a flowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an oozing, of tears:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grief without weeping:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabaraAtN","text_ar":"عَبَرَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EabarN","text_ar":"عَبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (so in the O, [but this, if correct, is a quasi-pl. n.,]) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibarN","text_ar":"عِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Thus in copies of the K.) Of the first meaning, the following is an ex.:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA_in~a $ifaAy^iY EaborapN lawo safaHotuhaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And verily my cure would be a tear if I shed it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and of the last, the following is an ex.:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"laka maA A^abokiY walaA Eaborapa biY"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some relate it,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wlA Ebrp liY","text_ar":"ولا عبرة لِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For thy sake I weep, but there is grief in me for myself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says As: (TA:) or in this saying, which is a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be redundant, or it may be what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maSodariy~ap","text_ar":"مَصْدَرِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"For thee I weep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for thee is my weeping, I"},{"kind":"text","text":"[myself]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having no need of weeping."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Meyd.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","A","K","S","O"]},{"entry_id":"n27833","headword_ar":"عِبْرَةٌ","root":"Ebr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"a subst. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAiEotibaAru","text_ar":"الاِعْتِبَارُ"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An admonition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exhortation:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in iii. 11):"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an admonition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exhortation, by which one takes warning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"example:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel in xxiii. 21:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing by the state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition, of which one is admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reminded, and guided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"directed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xxiii. 21:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[lit."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a being admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reminded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; but meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of being admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a warning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an example"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Jel in xvi. 68:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN bimaA maDaY","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ بِمَا مَضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ait~EaAZN","text_ar":"اِتّعَاظٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta*ak~urN","text_ar":"تَذَكُّرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning, in like manner,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cause of being admonished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reminded, by what has passed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an indication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd and Jel in xxiv. 44, and Bd in xvi. 68,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby one passes from ignorance to knowledge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd in xvi. 68:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a state"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of things"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"circumstances"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whereby, from the knowledge of what is seen, one arrives at the knowledge of what is not seen;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (B, TA:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wonderful thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as serves as a warning"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an example"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibarN","text_ar":"عِبَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) ―         -b2-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"account,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"regard, in which a thing is held in respect of predicamental order;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiEotibaArN","text_ar":"اِعْتِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [Hence the common phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA Eiborapa bihi","text_ar":"لَا عِبْرَةَ بِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"No regard is due to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"]       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EibaArapN","text_ar":"عِبَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","B","TA","A","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}